The paper deals with wireless communication systems and their performance analysis, which falls under the scope of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on Device-to-Device (D2D) and Machine-to-Machine (M2M) communications, which are subfields of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of multiple access channels and joint decoding, which are topics in Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with Machine-Type Devices (MTDs), which are a type of Internet of Things (IoT) device, falling under the scope of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of the proposed system, which falls under the scope of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
